Static vs final vs Static final keyword in java.

Static keyword :
 0. Variables can be re-initialized after declaration.
 1. It is not compulsory to initialize the static variable at the time of its declaration.
  
  
final keyword :
 0. Variables cannot be re-initialized after declaration.
 1. It is compulsory to initialize the final variable at the time of its declaration.


Static final keyword :
 0. It is the combination of both Static and final keywords.
 1. Variable that is global to class and is impossible to change.
